values:
yeah, so i remember why i abandoned my 10 other livejournals.

not only does nothing ever happen that interests me, theres even less that interests you.

AND you dont read it, aye?

aye...

(or you care for a day. then stop. yeah. thats more commmon)
http://iamsynthetic.livejournal.com/2947.html

currently, its 10:55 on monday morning and im boring myself to tears with this terrible computer class. nobody is online to entertain me while i type whore on the loudest keyboard ever. in a room where everybody should be paying attentino. i think the teacher is offended im not paying attention.

im also about to die. i got no sleep except an hour. an hour. who can survive on one hour of sleep? on a day where ill be at class for oh-so-long.

you know who you are. and you know i blame you. 

grr.
http://iamsynthetic.livejournal.com/2808.html

cara. youre a crazy girl. crazy girl.

im glad im not an unhip, uncool square. you can lavish me with more unflattery later, thanks.

and rick. rick, youre a crazy crazy fella.  and be it as you may not read this. im still better than you at pac man.  inky blinky pinky sue for ms pac man. inky blinky pinky clyde for regular. so while i was wrong on the game title, you were wrong at life. woo.

rock the boat.
http://iamsynthetic.livejournal.com/2399.html

and you have proven that good things can happen to good persons!

....if only i were that good person.
http://iamsynthetic.livejournal.com/2163.html

knowing full well that you wont read this before its too late.....


WISH ME LUCK ON MY INTERVIEW
http://iamsynthetic.livejournal.com/1969.html

same shit. different day.

went to class. came home.
slept.
went to class. went out.
had a time. got sick over jack and the box. got jealous over star wars trilogy not being mine. much ado about nothing.

came home. whined about it on my journal. yadda yadda. perhaps tomorrow will be more exciting.  going to apply at gamestop, where my MAD HOOKUPS might get me a job to fill my target void.  bon soir!
http://iamsynthetic.livejournal.com/1615.html

today. nothing exciting. i uh. went to school. i uh. came back from school. 

a girl hung up on me. i went to school. i came back from school.

the girl didnt call me back. so then i sat around in the dark and cried all day about it.
http://iamsynthetic.livejournal.com/1408.html

all envy me! im soon to be jobless.  my two weeks were put in from that nazi-esque job at target. and now i have to find a better job. great.

but what more can i do...

beh, im too lazy to write it all. ask me. (HAHHAHA)
http://iamsynthetic.livejournal.com/1094.html

well. an entirely unexpected wave of goodness. my saturday night didnt suck.

after being at work, which entirely sucked, having been given more work than any person who works at target, i followed it up with a nice coffee with john, kim, and ...stephanie.

stephanie is an asu student majoring in womens studies.  shes a vegan lesbian complete with gender-neutral clothing. got the tongue bar, got the tattoos.  most fun girl ever. loud, outspoken, and a feminist who DOESNT GET DEFENSIVE. 

something has gone right when within 5 minutes of knowing her, you can make a crack at her feminism/lesbianism, and she can come right back at you with some impressive quip.  she knows how to tell a story. she knows how to tell terrible stories well.

so, subtract the feminist part. subtract the lesbian part. subract the vegan part. its a wonder shes unattached. its also nice when they have a sense of humor. why dont more girls have that?  either way. it was exciting to learn what different color handkerchiefs in different pockets mean on gay people.  different strokes for different folks leads to the best conversation ever. ranging from lactating and nipple piercing to acid-tripping raving. ahh. 

why cant more strangers be this instantly comfortable?
http://iamsynthetic.livejournal.com/856.html

what exactly goes on in a livejournal?  lets see what happens when i write like THE REST OF YOU do.

so yeah um. i woke up this morning. got on the computer AND WAS RUDELY SURPRISED THAT... nothing at all exciting had happened. uh. today ill be going through the routine measures of waking up, spending 4 hours on the computer. standing up from the chair. showering. dressing. driving. working. drive home. (and maybe. since its saturday. drink myself into some sort of catatonic state. then run about the streets in a fashion not unalike will ferell in OLD SCHOOL.)

but if that doesnt happen. more than likely im going to be right back here. typing in my journal about how much i hate asian camera shoppers.

you never know, do you?



oh, and if youre wondering how i can run about the streets ina catatonic state. well. surely youve never been drunk
